  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Summary/Objective</strong></u><br />The person is to assist the Finance Manager & Senior Accountant and is responsible for all areas relating to preparation and review of financial reporting with a tight deadline. This position will be responsible for ensuring timely reporting in compliance with accounting principles, practices and procedures.<br /><br /><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Review subsidiaries’ management accounts</li><li> Preparation of group consolidation report</li><li>Perform intercompany reconciliations, eliminations and consolidation adjustments</li><li>Provide financial analysis, variance explanations and key insights</li><li> Approve documents within ERP system as per workflow processes</li><li> GST reviews and submission</li><li>Act as key liaison with auditors for group and entity-level audits</li><li>Coordinate audit timelines and resolve audit queries efficiently</li><li>Draft financial statements, audit reports and notes to accounts</li><li>Support annual return and statutory filing processes</li><li>Preparation of tax schedules and assist in the replies to tax agent for corporate tax filings</li><li>Assist in preparation of transfer pricing documentation</li><li>Assist in system implementation</li><li>Provide administrative support and perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned</li></ul><p><u><strong>Competencies</strong></u></p><ul><li>Excellent time management and able to prioritize work assigned</li><li>Ability to multitask, work under pressure and meet deadlines required</li><li> Strong verbal and written communication skills</li><li> Commitment to working efficiently and accurately</li><li>Meticulous and being thorough in completing work tasks</li><li>Professional manner and strong ethical code</li><li>Strong interpersonal, supervisory and customer service skills</li></ul>",
